<p>I have an ajax table click event that gets database data according to the clicked name from the first table and display the second table with employee information. The problem now is that the employee information data only pile up in the second table, I want to refresh the second table every name that the user clicked. By the way  the second table is inside a div tag. Here is my ajax code:</p>  <pre><code>function putThis(control){ var getid = control.innerText; var first = $("#from[name=from]").val(); var second = $("#to[name=to]").val(); $.ajax({     type:'POST',     url: 'testtable.php',     data: {id: getid,from: first,to: second},     cache: false,     global: false,     success:function(data)     {     $("#result").append(data);     alert("Success: " + getid + " " + first + " to " + second);     } }); } </code></pre>